{
  "texts": [
    "While these hardness proofs mainly focused on the case that the secret key is sampled from the uniform distribution, there are also reductions from LWE with uniform secret to LWE with some other secret key distributions, including the error distribution",
    "[ACPS09], a uniform binary distribution [BLP + 13], and a sparse binary distribution [CHK + 16].",
    "RLWE (resp.",
    "GLWE) is proved to be at least as hard as worst-case lattice hard problems over ideal (resp.",
    "module) lattices [LPR10, LPR13, PRS17, LS15]."
  ]
}